descriptiveMetadata.title: Laboratory Notebook

names.fullForm: Portsmouth, Isaac Newton Wallop, Earl of, 1825-1891

descriptiveMetadata.abstract:
Newton's notes on optics, precious stones, colours, temperatures, salts, medical matters, alchemy and other subjects, in English and Latin, c. 1669-c.1693.

The last four pages are written in upside-down from the back, and so numbered in reverse order 344-341.


A full description and transcription of this manuscript is available at The Chymistry of Isaac Newton
subject: Chemistry - Early works to 1800
Optics - Early works to 1800
Alchemy - Early works to 1800
ownership: From the Portsmouth Collection, donated by the fifth Earl of Portsmouth, 1872.
